From: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 12:43:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "ice: Remove jumbo_remove step from TX path"
References: bsc#1258210
Patch-mainline: 6.18.34
Git-commit: 18a08b87db713d50b4fb0ff3e971c36f6610c666

This reverts commit 55500245ec0420df96b2a89444aabf0cff2c60bc.

Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_txrx.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_txrx.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_txrx.c
index 90dbe5266ce7..73f08d02f9c7 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_txrx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_txrx.c
@@ -2594,6 +2594,9 @@ ice_xmit_frame_ring(struct sk_buff *skb, struct ice_tx_ring *tx_ring)
 
 	ice_trace(xmit_frame_ring, tx_ring, skb);
 
+	if (unlikely(ipv6_hopopt_jumbo_remove(skb)))
+		goto out_drop;
+
 	count = ice_xmit_desc_count(skb);
 	if (ice_chk_linearize(skb, count)) {
 		if (__skb_linearize(skb))
-- 
